The Pan-Africanist Congress says it would have performed much better in the recent general elections if it had more funding. The party managed to score less than half a percent , securing just one seat in Parliament. President Narius Moloto briefed the media in Johannesburg earlier on Saturday. “The PAC is not being funded. We’ve being funding ourselves against parties that have invested millions into the elections. We have not been able to reach our people the way we thought we could. But it’s one of the serious impediments and going into the future we will address it.” Click below for more on the story:  